buildObject

public Object buildObject(Class c,
                          String s)
                   throws FilterTextParsingException
Description copied from interface: ITypesFactory

Builds an object out of the passed string, with the given type.

The object's type must match the passed class

If the factory cannot build the given type, it can return the passed string; in this case, the method ITypesFactory.getBuildType(Class) must provide this information

If the string cannot be parsed into the expected type, the implementation can raise an exception, or simply return null
